programme.title: Human Prey: Killers of the Savannah
programme.desc: Focused on helping a pregnant, wounded lioness, an unarmed South African conservationist unwittingly ends up face-to-face with one of the pride's aggressive, young males. During his Zambezi River adventure, a pilot is attacked by a hungry hyena.

programme.title: Human Prey: Killer Bears
programme.desc: While hiking through Montana's Glacier National Park, Johan and Jenna Otter are attacked by a raging grizzly intent on protecting her cubs. In a remote British Columbia nature park, Patti and Kelly McConnell are mauled by a hungry 400-pound black bear.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: A 19th century legend has put the town of Rhinelander, Wisconsin on the map, a must-visit location for those interested in American folklore and the supernatural, as Rhinelander is the home of the Hodag, a mythical beast transformed into a town mascot.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: Each year, tourists with no interest in skiing or scenic views flock to the Austrian town of Klagenfurt to do a different kind of sightseeing: they’re after a glimpse of the legendary Tatzelwurm creature, or the chance to drink a beer and discuss it.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: The town of Willow Creek, California takes the legend of Bigfoot more seriously than anywhere else in the world. An ape-like monster believed to be the missing link, there are organized hunting expeditions, statues, and even a museum. But how real is it?

programme.title: Helicopter ER: Family Horror
programme.desc: A family outing ends in horror for a young mother after a seaside crash, and the flying doctors and paramedics of the Yorkshire Air Ambulance rush to find a victim's severed finger.

programme.title: Helicopter ER: On the Way to School
programme.desc: A freak farm accident is caught on CCTV and the team is scrambled to rescue the three young victims. Paramedic Andy fights to save a five-year-old boy run over on his way to school and there's a tricky rescue in a ravine in the Dales.

programme.title: Helicopter ER: DIY Gone Wrong
programme.desc: The Yorkshire Air Ambulance swoops onto a suburban bowling green to help a woman fighting to save her husband's life after a DIY accident, and in the Dales a cyclist goes into cardiac arrest after a wasp sting.

programme.title: Helicopter ER: Call in the Coastguard
programme.desc: A high-speed crash leaves a mother and child trapped in their wrecked car. Plus, paramedics Paul and James call in a coastguard chopper to help save a climber critically injured on Yorkshire's biggest natural landmark.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Cape Coast: Where Worlds Colide
programme.desc: Watch Africa's Cape Coast that goes from the frigid waters of Cape Point to the sub-tropic seas of Kwazulu-Natal.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Congo: the Untamed Heart
programme.desc: Known for centuries as Africa's Dark Heart, the Congo is a multi-layered, three-dimensional world, seething with innumerable species. By peeling back the layers, we discover how this vast rainforest works, and expose the hidden lives of its inhabitants.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Sahara: Life on the Edge
programme.desc: Watch Africa's Cape Coast that goes from the frigid waters of Cape Point to the sub-tropic seas of Kwazulu-Natal./After, see Africa's Dark Heart in the Congo which is seething with innumerable species./Last,learn about the largest desert in the world.

programme.title: Wildest Africa: Lake Turkana: Land of the Crocodile
programme.desc: The largest of Africa's Rift valley lakes, Lake Turkana is at the heart of one of the harshest landscapes on the planet. Despite its hostile environment, man and beast have both worked out a way to survive.

programme.title: Snake Boss: Double Trouble
programme.desc: Julia confronts her fear on heights while trying to wrangle a massive carpet python. Meanwhile, Johnny Must try to catch two of them. Later Julia has a close call with the worlds second deadliest snake.

programme.title: Snake Boss: A Sorry Tail
programme.desc: Julia saves a karate school from a highly venomous visitor. Meanwhile, Johnny Bagpipes leaves his lady flying solo as he prepares to fly to Rome.

programme.title: Snake Boss: Stuck in the Middle with You
programme.desc: Julia teams up with a terrier to track down a suspected deadly intruder. Meanwhile, she rescues Bob from a tetchy python, and comes up with a great marketing idea.

programme.title: Snake Boss: Bird Appétit
programme.desc: It is a snake snack-o-rama. Johnny and Julia rescue a pet budgie before its too late. Johnny wrangles another python. And the both of them welcome a new member to the snake catching team.

programme.title: Snake Boss: It's Not Easy Being Green
programme.desc: Julia faces off against an unwelcome house guest in the form of an inquisitive serpent. Meanwhile, the new member of the team, Bonny, goes to doggy boot camp.

programme.title: Snake Boss: The Fear Factor
programme.desc: It's all about the fear factor this time, as Julia deals with a potted threat first, before catching a tiny house dweller, and scaling a rooftop to rescue a big snake.

programme.title: Snake Boss: Life and Death
programme.desc: Julia comes to the aid of a dehydrated python who needs to be taken to the RSPCA, and there's a remarkable confrontation between a Keelback and a highly poisonous cane toad.

programme.title: Snake Boss: Two Boys and a Shoe Box
programme.desc: Julia will get a love-bite from her favorite snake, Bonny the dog continues her snake detection training, and then there's a deadly wrangle with a juvenile eastern brown.

programme.title: Snake Boss: All in a Hard Day's Work
programme.desc: Training is in full flow for Bonny the dog on her quest to sniff out snakes, but Julia is called poolside to fish out one cool snake, before facing an extremely close call.

programme.title: Snake Boss: What a Catch!
programme.desc: Julia will be cooped up with a massive eastern brown, while Bonny gets her first taste of snake hunting, and Johnny ultimately makes his biggest catch yet.

programme.title: Boogeymen
programme.desc: What is it about sleepy Adams, Tennessee, that attracts tourists eager to visit graveyards, haunted caves and cabins, swap scary stories and try to summon the spirits of the dead? The legend of the Bell Witch and a 200-year old haunting are they key.

programme.title: The Immigrant
programme.desc: 1921. An innocent immigrant woman is tricked into a life of burlesque and vaudeville until a dazzling magician tries to save her and reunite her with her sister who is being held in the confines of Ellis Island. Starring: Marion Cotillard, Joaquin Phoenix.

programme.title: Two Lovers
programme.desc: A Brooklyn-set romantic drama about a bachelor torn between the family friend his parents wish he would marry and his beautiful but volatile new neighbor. Starring: Joaquin Phoenix, Gwyneth Paltrow, Vinessa Shaw.

programme.title: A Woman Hunted
programme.desc: A young mother (Alexandra Paul) is released from drug rehabilitation and trying to get custody of her daughters (Chelsea Ceci and Tanya Trombetta) when she becomes a suspect in the murder of a professional athlete (Tim Post).

programme.title: Christmas in Wonderland
programme.desc: Starring Matthew Knight and Chris Kattan. Three children and their father move from California to Canada. When they go shopping at the mall, they find counterfeit cash, inadvertently help catch crooks, and make a discovery about Santa.

programme.title: Help! I've Shrunk The Family
programme.desc: A lonely 9 year old boy makes a new friend when he discovers a magical little man inside a cupboard, but when one of the man's spells goes awry, the boy's entire family is shrunk down to four inches in height.

programme.title: Holiday in Your Heart
programme.desc: Fourteen-year-old LeAnn Rimes wants nothing more than to sing at the Grand Ole Opry. She is invited to sing at a Christmas concert on Nashville's famous stage, but upon her arrival, she is faced with a difficult decision.

programme.title: Antboy
programme.desc: 12-year-old Pelle is bitten by an ant and develops superpowers. Aided by comic book nerd Wilhelm, Pelle creates a secret identity as superhero Antboy.

programme.title: Paper Heart
programme.desc: Charlyne Yi embarks on a quest across America to make a documentary about the one subject she doesn't fully understand: love.

programme.title: Finding Mrs. Claus
programme.desc: When Mrs. Claus (Mira Sorvino) feels neglected by her less than attentive husband (Will Sasso), she goes to Las Vegas to help a little girl with her Christmas wish.

programme.title: LEGEND OF KUNG FU RABBIT
programme.desc: In order to keep his promise to the ageing kung fu master, Fu, the lovable rabbit, must embark on a heroic quest to rescue young Penny and defeat the villainous panda Slash.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Danger Death Ray
programme.desc: Danger Death Ray: A slick secret agent investigates an evil organization that stole a top secret death ray.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Samson vs. The Vampire Women
programme.desc: While Mike and the Bots wrestle with Samson vs. the Vampire Women, TV's Frank is assumed into Second Banana Heaven.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: The Violent Years
programme.desc: Jam Handy shows the world the glory of sexism with electric kitchen appliances and Ed Wood analyzes the world of criminals spoiled by their parents.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: The Incredibly Strange Creatures Who Stopped Living and Became Mixed-Up Zombies
programme.desc: A couple of slackers stumble across a cult of monsters at a carnival.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Gorgo
programme.desc: Greedy sailors capture a giant lizard off the coast of Ireland and sell it to a London circus. Then its mother shows up.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Devil Fish
programme.desc: When Dr. Stella Dickens concludes the recent string of grisly deaths and demolished boats can’t be the result of any known marine creature, she sets out to capture the beast, a genetically created bioweapon that must be kept secret . . . at any cost.

programme.title: Overdrawn At The Memory Bank
programme.desc: A weather tech's mind gets trapped in a computer and Pearl establishes her own public television pledge program.

programme.title: The Pumaman
programme.desc: A man learns he was born with special powers and becomes the superhero Puma Man. He fights the villainous Dr. Kobras, who uses an ancient mind-control mask in his attempts to rule the world.

programme.title: Mystery Science Theater 3000: Cave Dwellers
programme.desc: Newly-married wife Jenni can't tell if the skull she sees in her new home is a ghostly apparition of her husband's dead first wife, hallucinations from her own nervous condition... or something else.

programme.title: The Incredibly Strange Creatures Who Stopped Living and Became Mixed-Up Zombies
programme.desc: A couple of slackers stumble across a cult of monsters at a carnival.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Maniac
programme.desc: Maniac starts when a Vaudeville-impersonator-turned-lab-assistant-to-a-mad-scientist refuses his bosses reasonable request that he shoot himself in the heart and offer his corpse as an experimental subject. After that, it starts to get strange.

programme.title: RiffTrax Presents: King of Kong Island
programme.desc: King of Kong Island is the action-packed tale of a scantily-clad jungle girl, some people who speak English without seeming to understand it and without bothering to move their lips, a mad scientist friend of theirs and their very many cigarettes.

programme.title: RiffTrax: RiffTrax Special 90s Cyber Thrillers: RiffTrax Special 90s Cyber Thrillers
programme.desc: Time to grab a stack of floppy disks, or maybe 2 of those shiny CD-ROMs we've been hearing about, and boot up the very first RiffTrax Special! The topic? 90s Cyber Thrillers.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Abraxas: Guardian of the Universe
programme.desc: Abraxas, Guardian of the Universe, follows the heroic exploits of a galactic defender, played by Jesse Ventura, who comes to Earth to-wait, wait, that can't be right.

programme.title: RiffTrax Presents: Horror Express
programme.desc: The Deadly Mantis showed us that the life of a palaeontologist is one of intrigue, romance, and unstoppable monsters. Horror Express does nothing to dispel this notion, so that presumably means it can only be true.

programme.title: RiffTrax Live: "Manos" the Hands of Fate: RiffTrax Live: "Manos" the Hands of Fate
programme.desc: From the stars of Mystery Science Theater 3000 comes RiffTrax, hilarious audio commentaries for your favorite - and not-so-favorite - movies!

programme.title: RiffTrax: Best of RiffTrax Villains: Best of RiffTrax Villains
RiffTrax: The Mesa of Lost Women: The Mesa of Lost Women (S1E59)
programme.desc: Mesa of Lost Women! Not to be confused with the Plateau of Misplaced Babes, the Bayou of Wandering Broads, or the Tundra of Girlfriends Who Keep Trying to Get You to Ask for Directions but You're Simply Just Too Foolish and Proud.

programme.title: RiffTrax: R.O.T.O.R.: R.O.T.O.R.
programme.desc: Coldyron! Research! Shoeboogie! If you say those words real fast they kind of sound like a song, but they're also three of the many reasons you should join Mike, Kevin, and Bill for the wonder of wonders that is R.O.T.O.R.!

programme.title: RiffTrax: Superheroes!: Superheroes!
programme.desc: Welcome to RiffTrax Shorts: Superheroes, three short films that teach us it takes more than tights and a cape to be a superhero. Sometimes, it takes a Mylar jumpsuit and a garbage can lid. Featuring Batman, Measuring Man, and Safety Woman!

programme.title: Reefer Madness: Three Riffer Edition!
programme.desc: Yes, Reefer Madness let the world know that even a single dose of marijuana caused insane laughter, enhanced skill at ragtime piano, the inability to avoid hitting old men with your car, and defenestration.

programme.title: RiffTrax: Plan 9 From Outer Space: Plan 9 From Outer Space
programme.desc: There have been many, many Plan 9s all throughout history, some of them more successful than others, all of them terrestrial - it took a man with the vision of Ed Wood to show us the very real horrors of a Plan 9 from Outer Space!

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: The Fugitive
programme.desc: Oggy catches Dee-Dee red-handed stealing food from his fridge. In order to run away from the cat's hold, the cockroach pretends to be dead. His fellows and accomplices immediately call the police and Oggy is charged with murder!

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Invincible
programme.desc: While chasing the roaches on the roof, Oggy crashes on the ground. His head is as flat as a pancake, but when he stands up, he doesn't feel any pain and refuses Jack's help! Jack is convinced that Oggy has become an invincible super hero.

programme.title: Oggy and the Cockroaches: Oggy and the Magic Smile
programme.desc: Oggy buys a cardboard smile in a joke shop. When he puts the cardboard smile on his face, he is immediately transformed into a muscular, super confident athlete! And everyone is hypnotized by the vibes he gives off. They cater to his slightest whim.

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 10
programme.desc: Super-Noms are back! Join Om Nom and Om Nelle on a thrilling journey to fight the Evil Spider and his minions! Meet new characters, travel to peculiar locations and check out the new amazing gadgets that Professor has invented!

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 11
programme.desc: Super-Noms like attending different events, but somehow an adventure awaits wherever they come ... Watch Om Nom and Om Nelle turn evil into good in this new season!

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 1
programme.desc: Om Nom, the hero of the world-famous Cut the Rope game series, is a cute little candy-eating monster. One day, he mysteriously shows up at the doorstep of one boy's house, and this marked the beginning of many fun adventures.

programme.title: Om Nom Stories: Episode 2
programme.desc: Just when Om Nom thought all of the adventures are behind him and he can finally get some rest with the bowl of candies in hand, something unexpected happened ... Visit breathtaking locations and meet amazing new creatures in Om Nom Stories!

programme.title: Lucky Fred: San Juan Night / Braianna-Bot
programme.desc: Extraterrestrial moths are attacking the Earth, Brains must stop them and she will need Friday's help. / Fred wants to know what the girls' secrets are and orders Friday to pretend to be Brains to join their club ...

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Friday Gets Recalled / Fred's Game
programme.desc: Brains receives a new robot, the X-bot 9000, which is more sophisticated than Friday. But Brains gets quickly sick of the new model ... / Fred is chosen to be the goalkeeper at a football game but Wally K. is the striker for the other team ...

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Books and Roses / The Short Report
programme.desc: Today is Sant Jordi's Day and Fred wants to give Nora a rose. But there are ten other boys who have the same idea ... / A gossip blog publishes explosive photos of students at Fred's school – and now also details about aliens!

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Fred Gets Crushed / Dusty Rides Again
programme.desc: Braianna and Sir Percival are acting very strange. Fred suspects that they are dating ... / Friday is having a good time with his new robot friend Dusty. But one day his new buddy goes way too far ...

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Mister Perfect / Afternoon Off
programme.desc: Eddie is a talented sitar player who has enchanted Nora with his music. Fred is jealous and tries everything to win Nora over. / Brains bets with Fred that he can't spend a single afternoon without him.

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Squirrel Scare / The Big Picture
programme.desc: Brains is terrified of squirrels and even programs a machine to suck them up ... / Mr. Fractal is confiscating Mort's phone including a picture of Brains fighting an alien!

programme.title: Lucky Fred: Unlucky Fred / Love Deodorant
programme.desc: Fred has lost his lucky dice in an amusement park. To find them again, he decides to turn Friday into a new pair of dice ... / Fred causes confusion with a perfume from space ...

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: Lights, Camera, Goldfish!
programme.desc: When Admiral Bubbles tricks Beanie into emailing pages from his diary to the producers of the "Detechnoman Movie", they mistakenly assume that the outrageous tales are a pitch for the script, and he is soon hired to work on the film.

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: Ghostfish!
programme.desc: When Beanie's Mom joins Mrs. Prehistoritch in a comical séance to ask Mrs. Prehistoritch's late husband Ernie about the location of her favorite golf ball, the proceedings give the Goldfish an idea.

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: The Great Outdoors!
programme.desc: Beanie, his Mom, and Elwood head to family summer camp, and Beanie brings his evil pet to keep him under control. But the camp turns out to be run by a city-slicker who doesn't know the first thing about nature!

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: A Schoolplay Named Disaster!
programme.desc: Admiral Bubbles has perfected his electrified ink process which allows him to control paper and manipulate it into dangerous forms, as he quickly proves by attacking Beanie with a paper dragon.

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: Grade-A Goldfish!
programme.desc: When Beanie fails a test at school, Admiral Bubbles convinces him to let him plant a small transceiver in his mouth so that Admiral Bubbles can transmit Beanie the answers to his next test.

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: Scoop Gets Scooped!
programme.desc: Unable to sleep, Beanie witnesses his newsstand buddy Scoop getting kidnapped by two hooded figures. Realizing that he lacks the goldfish's knowledge about underworld dealings, Beanie is forced to ask for Admiral Bubbles' help.

programme.title: My Goldfish is Evil: Derailed!
programme.desc: While Beanie and his Nana are dropping off Mom at the train station, Admiral Bubbles temporarily escapes, and makes his way to the station control station where he discovers that an experimental amphibious Air Force jet is on one of the trains.

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Compound Compromised
programme.desc: On a trip to Rio to play Brazilian masters-of-flair, Club Palmentieri, Supa Strikas are demolished in a “friendly” beach game. The only person who can help them is a legend of the game ... who has been missing for thirty years!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Blasts From The Past
Supa Strikas: Between Friends
programme.desc: Supa Strikas travel to Mexico to confront the biggest goalkeeper in the Super League. Shakes uncovers De Los Santos’ past, and makes an amazing discovery in the big man’s hometown: mysterious Aztec ruins ... and the origins of the game itself!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Instinct Extinct
programme.desc: Supa Strikas face Twisting Tiger’s old team, FC Nakama, but Nakama boss Ura Giri releases a DVD of all Tiger’s secret moves to punish him for leaving the team. Now the famous midfielder needs to find new moves ... and fast!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: Big Bo Lockdown
programme.desc: Pressure is on as Supa Strikas arrive in Spain to play Barka FC and star striker, Riano. But Shakes gets some training from Riano’s old Coach, Golare, which turns out to be less than helpful!

programme.title: Supa Strikas: The End Of Dreams
programme.desc: Big Bo helps local prison inmates by training their soccer team. But Knuckles, a nasty convict, looks just like the great goalkeeper and switches places with Big Bo! How will he escape in time for Supa Strikas’ epic game against the mighty FC Colossus?

programme.title: Supa Strikas: No 'El' in Team
programme.desc: After a mishap with the bumbling Professor, his coffee, and the state-of-the-art Match Measure Machine, things go horribly wrong with Shakes’ exercise plan!

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: The Ghastly Ghost
programme.desc: Marina wakes a pirate's ghost - who promptly moves in with her. She thinks he's funny at first, but the pirate soon wears out his welcome. How can you lay hands on a ghost and get rid of him? Fortunately, the pirate has a hermit-crab phobia.

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: Hundreds of Kids and Counting
programme.desc: Bernie adopts hundreds of cute little abandoned baby hermit-crabs. He builds them a little playground where they can hang out and play. But when Zig shows up to nab a few little toddlers for dinner, they don't turn out to be quite that cute.

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: Santa Zig
programme.desc: It's Christmas! Zig decides to dress up as Santa Claus and deliver a present to Marina (and grab her at the same time). But with his coconut palm sleigh and seals instead of reindeer, discretion is not the first word that comes to mind.

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: Goin' Home
programme.desc: Zig finds a book about African wildlife and realises that's where he actually comes from. He decides to go there and meet his compatriots. But hyenas are not very popular and no one is nice to him. Sharko and Marina miss him, and get depressed.

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: The Return of the Crazy Dolphin
programme.desc: After a new series of unsuccessful attempts to make off with the mermaid, Zig decides to drop the whole thing and become a vegetarian. Even the wildest, most far-out inventions of Bernie aren't enough to prod him back into action.

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: Loony Cruise
programme.desc: Marina and Sharko board a luxury liner for a cruise disguised as humans... Zig and Bernie join as stowaways. When Sharko's identity is discovered, all humans leave ship. Bernie is assigned to the helm, while the usual chase takes place on board.

programme.title: Zig & Sharko: Bernie Moves House
programme.desc: An underwater volcanic eruption gives birth to a second island. Bernie, who has had an argument with Zig, decides to move there. While Zig has to fend for himself, Bernie builds a dream house, and parties it up with Sharko and Marina.

programme.desc: Akiza goes to get her Turbo Dueling license, but before she can drive off into the sunset, she first has to out-duel, out-maneuver and out-smart one of Sector Security's finest for her final exam.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Syd is Vicious
programme.desc: After a string of Duel Runner thefts has New Domino City on high alert, Jack Atlas decides to take justice into his own hands and ventures out in search of those responsible.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Dawn of the Duel Board: Part I
programme.desc: When a mysterious new student gives Luna a-one-of-a-kind Duel Board, Leo, trusting his instincts, steps up and tries to pull a 180 on their friendship.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Dawn of the Duel Board: Part II
programme.desc: As the Duel Board battle between Leo, Luna and the mystery duelist continues, Leo soon realizes that their mysterious opponent is actually an all-too-familiar friend.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's
programme.desc: Jack and Crow set out to find a restless Yusei - hoping to ease his mind and reinforce the friendship they share by Turbo Dueling down memory lane.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: The Super Genius
programme.desc: A mysterious amnesiac helps Yusei build a new engine program for his Runner, but before they can test it out, a make-up-wearing, noodle-eating crook runs off with the file.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Get With the Program: Part I
programme.desc: Yusei and the gang trail Lazar to the local mall hoping to reacquire the engine design program that this window-shopping, noodle-eating crook stole from them.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Get With the Program: Part II
programme.desc: Yusei and Lazar are trapped in a warehouse where their only chance of escaping is if Yusei can outduel a Guard Bot whose CPU has been uploaded with all of Yusei's battle techniques.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Will The Real Jack Atlas, Please Stand Up: Part I
programme.desc: After being charged with crimes he didn't commit, Jack Atlas scrambles to uncover the truth before his friends and fans turn their back on him for good.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Will The Real Jack Atlas, Please Stand Up: Part II
programme.desc: With Jack Atlas on the run, Yusei and Crow set out in search of their pal, hoping to clear his good name before bad turns to worse.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Mother Knows Best
programme.desc: When Zora's stubborn son Leon suddenly returns home, Crow picks a duel with him to help him realize that the ongoing quarrel he has with his mother is much ado about nothing.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Duelist For Hire
programme.desc: When Yusei heads to a tumbleweed town at the request of some locals, he quickly finds himself in the middle of two feuding families - with his old friend Kalin right there with him!

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Showdown at Sundown: Part I
programme.desc: When Yusei challenges Kalin to a duel, he hopes to save his old acquaintance from a terrible fate. However, the dueling gets dicey when it becomes clear that Kalin doesn't necessarily want to be saved!

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Showdown at Sundown: Part II
programme.desc: As Yusei continues to duel his best to save Kalin from a most unhappy ending, he suddenly finds himself double crossed by his supposed allies and in desperate need of some saving of his own!

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: The Race to Escape: Part I
programme.desc: After being double crossed and sent to the mines by his supposed allies, Yusei hatches a plan to escape. Can Yusei find a way out, or will he and Kalin be forced to work the mines forever?

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: The Race to Escape: Part II
programme.desc: It's a high-speed minecart chase as Kalin and Yusei scramble to rescue Sergio's family from the clutches of the Crash Town mine. When Lawton and his goons gain up on the fleeing family, things take a heartbreaking turn.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Clash at Crash Town: Part I
programme.desc: The sinister Lawton has captured West and Nico and gained control of Crash Town, but Yusei and Kalin have no intention of letting him get away with it. It's the ultimate showdown as the dueling duo confront Lawton in a winner-takes-all battle.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Clash at Crash Town: Part II
programme.desc: As the clash between Lawton, Yusei and Kalin comes to a climactic close, Yusei and Kalin must figure out a way to defeat Lawton before his deck destroys their dreams of freeing everyone in the mines.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: The Question of the Card
programme.desc: When Sherry breaks into a city building in search of answers about a very special duel card, she finds a lot more than she bargained for.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Keeping a Promise: Part I
programme.desc: When Crow looks to avenge a missing colleague, he ends up finding an old friend who turns out not to be what he seems.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Keeping a Promise: Part II
programme.desc: Crow takes on an old friend in a duel to determine the truth about a colleague's mysterious disappearance.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Natural Instincts: Part I
programme.desc: A little fender bender turns into a friendly duel when Crow smashes into one of Team Unicorn's duelists on the tournament practice lanes only this was no accident and Team Unicorn's intentions are anything but friendly.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Natural Instincts: Part II
programme.desc: New threats are on the horizon and no one can be trusted. Sherry arrives to inform Yusei that she suspects the sinister forces of Iliaster have infiltrated the tournament.

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Power Plays
programme.desc: Can Jack and his power-packed deck bring down his opponent or will Andre's secret plan place Jack and Team 5D's on the brink of elimination?

programme.title: Yu-Gi-Oh! 5D's: Trouble for Team 5D's
programme.desc: With Team Unicorn taking the early lead against Team 5D's, all eyes turn to Akiza as she takes to the track hoping to take down Andre and even up the score.

programme.title: Girl Most Likely
programme.desc: A failed New York playwright awkwardly navigates the transition from Next Big Thing to Last Year's News. Starring: Kristen Wiig, Annette Bening, Matt Dillon, Natasha Lyonne.

programme.title: Behaving Badly
programme.desc: Teenager Rick Stevens has a crush on Nina Pennington. They form a friendship and embark on a rock n' roll journey together while Nina deals with her overbearing boyfriend, Kevin. Starring: Nat Wolff, Selena Gomez, Mary-Louise Parker.

programme.title: Crimebusters
programme.desc: An attempted robbery turns to be an unexpected recruitment when two unemployed men mistakenly break into a police office instead of a store. Feat: Terence Hill, Bud Spencer & David Huddleston.

programme.title: Killers 2: The Beast
programme.desc: Trapped in a maximum security insane asylum, a girl must escape not only the psychological demons which inhabit her own mind, but also a band of killers determined to silence her forever.

programme.title: Sharknado: Heart of Sharkness
programme.desc: Discover the untold story of David Moore, the filmmaker who first dreamed of sharks in a tornado and brought on disaster by using real sharks. The first SHARKNADO was to be a movie never seen, a crime never reported, a tale never told. Until now.

programme.title: Izzie's Way Home
programme.desc: A constantly picked-on aquarium fish escapes her yacht home, unaware of the dangers that await her in the open ocean. With the help of other misfit sea creatures, she learns not only how to brave the perils of the deep, but how to be true to herself.

programme.title: Pirates of Treasure Island
programme.desc: An innkeeper's life of monotony suddenly changes when he comes into possession of a treasure map. Enlisting the help of Long John Silver and his band of cutthroat pirates, he sets off in search of the cursed Skeleton Island.

programme.title: In the Name of Ben-Hur
programme.desc: A young gladiator enslaved in the Roman arena in 171 A.D. escapes by chariot towards the freedom of Hadrian's Wall. Fighting centurions and mercenaries along the way, he becomes a folk hero for all those struggling to fight Roman oppression.

programme.title: Almighty Thor
programme.desc: When the demon god Loki destroys the fortress of Valhalla and steals the Hammer of Invincibility, only the young hero Thor can protect Earth from armageddon.

programme.title: Sunday School Musical
programme.desc: Two competing groups of high school students must rally together and enter a song and dance competition in order to save their church from closing.

programme.title: Merlin and the War of the Dragons
programme.desc: An army of dragons invade the crippled English countryside and the apprentice wizard Merlin must confront the fire-breathing beasts.

programme.title: Geo-Disaster
programme.desc: A family in the Northwest finds themselves in the center of a convergence of history's greatest disasters: a super volcano, a mega earthquake and a massive twister.

programme.title: 2010: Moby Dick
programme.desc: A modern adaptation of the classic novel of the captain of a high tech submarine and his obsessive quest to destroy the enormous prehistoric whale that maimed him.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Last Orders at The Fleece Inn
programme.desc: The team heads to Elland to investigate ghostly-goings on in this haunted pub. It's not just the spirits behind the bar lurking here. Multiple hauntings, murders and death surround this public house.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Liverpool's Secret Haunted Mansion
programme.desc: Bex and Sean delve deep into Woolton Hall, a derelict mansion in Liverpool. They appear to be forced out of the building by an unknown force and it takes its toll on one of the team members.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Celebrity Special - The Black Horse in Pluckley Village
programme.desc: Bex and Sean are joined by reality TV star Charlie Doherty in the most haunted village in the UK and investigate the most haunted pub in the UK, The Black Horse.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: The Night Before The Storm
programme.desc: In this special episode, it's the night before Sean and Bex are joined by their celebrity guest and they check out The Black Horse in Pluckley Village to investigate the paranormal hauntings at the most haunted pub in the UK.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: High Spirits at The Gothic Mansion
programme.desc: Bex and Sean investigate a haunting inside a gothic mansion, that is said to be haunted by the former owner of the building.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: The Blues Haunting at The Winslow Hotel
programme.desc: Bex, Sean and the team head to Liverpool and investigate a very famous hotel, which Everton football club supporters have frequented for over 100 years and it would appear that some of the guests have never checked out.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Fun and Games at The Sportsman Inn
programme.desc: Bex, Sean and Paul, investigate claims of paranormal incidents inside of a haunted inn. Once three separate cottages, will any of the previous residents join the investigation tonight? Or is there something more sinister haunting here?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Witches and Vampires Haunting St James Cemetery
programme.desc: St James Cemetery is set behind Liverpool Cathedral and is claimed to be the worlds most haunted, with the remains of over 58,000 people buried at the location and multiple claims of paranormal sightings.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension
programme.desc: Bex and Sean delve deep into a building that has survived world wars and is home to some very social ghosts. They come face to face with an angry spirit too, and something strange appears to be lurking in the basement.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: A Unexpected Haunted Adventure
programme.desc: The team heads to Lydiate Abbey to investigate claims of a ghostly white lady and stumble upon a totally hidden gem deep in the woods, which has its own spirits haunting.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Spirits Flying High at Speke Aerodrome
programme.desc: The team head to Speke Airport to investigate claims that some of the aircraft located there have ghostly passengers still aboard, waiting to take flight.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Bump In The Bingo Hall
Ghost Dimension
programme.desc: Hidden in St Helens, is a museum that is home to demonic and dark entities trapped inside of vehicles.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Jack The Ripper
programme.desc: Bex and Sean head to Sefton and investigate a police station connected to the murderous Jack The Ripper. Was James Maybrick really the Ripper? Did his wife poison him?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension
programme.desc: Could a tattoo studio be haunted? Has a Ouija board opened a gateway to the spirit dimension? Ghost Dimension spend the night investigating Deviant Ink tattoo studio.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Hotel of Horror
programme.desc: Ghost Dimension heads to Halewood and investigates the Wellington Hotel, believed to be a hive of paranormal activity. Will they uncover what is haunting this public house?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Who is There?
programme.desc: Could a cemetery be haunted? The team come head out to find out and contact restless souls that have been haunting the graveyard.

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: Man with a Cane
programme.desc: The team head to Bolton and investigate the Old Three Crowns. Haunted by the spirit of a very angry man with a deadly cane and an upset, young, ghostly girl, will they uncover why the girl is so upset? And could they encounter the angry spirit man?

programme.title: Ghost Dimension: I Hear a Baby Crying
programme.desc: The team investigate the Market Hotel in Bolton. Believed to be haunted by the lost soul of a previous landlord and a guest who likes to make herself known. They make contact with spirits from the other side and witness first hand paranormal activity.

programme.title: Pretty Persuasion
programme.desc: Evan Rachel Wood ("Westworld") stars in this black comedy about a 15-year-old student who incites chaos among her friends and launches a media frenzy when she accuses her drama teacher of sexual harassment.

programme.title: Mighty Aphrodite
programme.desc: When he discovers his adopted son is a genius, a New York sportswriter seeks out the boy's birth mother: a ditzy porn star and prostitute. Starring: Woody Allen, Mira Sorvino, Pamela Blair, Denise Faye, Marian Filali, Helena Bonham Carter.

programme.title: Wheeler
programme.desc: The story of an aspiring musician from Texas who travels to Nashville to fulfill his lifelong dream of trying his hand at country music. Starring: Stephen Dorff, Kris Kristofferson, Audrey Spillman.

programme.title: The Stream
programme.desc: In the summer of 1981, a tragedy of epic proportions sends five friends on an epic adventure. All they have to do is follow the stream to their destination and back. What could possibly go wrong? Starring: Mario Lopez, Christopher Gorham, Kelly Rutherford.

programme.title: Armless
programme.desc: In this off-kilter comedy, a woman comes to terms with her husband's strange secret: a compulsive desire to cut off his arms. \nThe film was an official selection of the 2010 Sundance Film Festival.

programme.title: Bernie
programme.desc: In small-town Texas, an affable mortician strikes up a friendship with a wealthy widow, though when she starts to become controlling, he goes to great lengths to separate himself from her grasp. Starring: Jack Black, Shirley MacLaine, Matthew McConaughey.

programme.title: Waking Ned
programme.desc: When a lottery winner dies of shock, his fellow townsfolk attempt to claim the money. Directed by Kirk Jones and starring Ian Bannen, David Kelly, and Fionnula Flanagan.

programme.title: Rise Of The Chupacabras
programme.desc: A treasure map leads a group of unsuspecting townsfolk to the lair of vampire-like creatures known as the Chupacabras.

programme.title: Small Time Crooks
programme.desc: A loser of a crook and his wife strike it rich when a botched bank job's cover business becomes a spectacular success. Starring: Woody Allen, Tracey Ullman, Hugh Grant, Michael Rapaport, Tony Darrow, Laurine Towler.

programme.title: The Dreamstone: The Daydream Bubble
programme.desc: The Dream Maker surprises Rufus and Amberley with a daydream bubble. Launched from Urpgor's cannon as oblivious test subjects, Blob, Nug and Frizz land in the daydream bubble. Also Zordrak's origin of evil is revealed.

programme.title: The Statue Collection
programme.desc: Zordrak sends the Urpneys to capture Pildit to add to his statue collections, using 'The Hand of Zordrak'. Rufus, Amberley and Albert crash the Urpneys' Whirlyped then they do battle with a one-eyed sea monster while Albert overcomes his aquaphobia.

programme.title: The Dreamstone: Argorrible Attack
programme.desc: Urpgor sends the Urpneys to transport the Argorribles to The Land of Dreams to give the Noops nightmares before the Dreamstone can act. The attack is successful so Rufus and Amberley retaliate in Viltheed with help from the Wuts.

programme.title: The Mad, Mad, Mad Monsters
programme.desc: A wedding for Frankenstein's monster and his bride, all of Universal's classic monsters come for the occasion.

programme.title: Tom and Jerry: Episode 1
programme.desc: A Swiss Track In The Bag The Tuba Tooter.

programme.title: Tom and Jerry: Episode 2
programme.desc: The Rocketeers Pots and Pans Piano Tooners.

programme.title: Tom and Jerry: Episode 3
programme.desc: Pencil Mania All's Well Fire Cheese.

programme.desc: Falling Hare Fresh Hare Case of the Missing Hare.

programme.title: What's Up Doc?: Episode 2
programme.desc: A Day at the Zoo Robin Hood Makes Good Pest Pupil Ding Dong Daddy.

programme.title: Alice Through the Looking Glass An Animated Classic
programme.desc: In this classic tale, Alice falls through a mirror and arrives in a wonderful place called Chessland! Alice's journey across eight crazy squares of Chessland is brought to the screen in this high quality entertaining animated feature for your kids.

programme.title: Attack Of The Super Monsters
programme.desc: In the year 2000 the dinosaurs reappear on planet Earth, terrorizing mankind.

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: Escape From Mongo
programme.desc: Flash's wife's life force is drained in Ming's Inquisitor but not before her essence is saved for Rick's nearly completed new super computer, Dynak X. In the first battle with Ming on Earth, our heroes are nearly electrocuted in an abandoned penitentiary.

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: The Creation Of Monitor
programme.desc: A huge cavern located in a dormant volcano is chosen as the new home for the Defenders of the Earth and their super computer Dynak X.

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: A Demon In His Pocket
programme.desc: Kshin's experiments with Mandrake's forbidden sorcery books produces Shogoth, an evil demon. It takes all the Defenders to defeat this creature. In the end, Kshin learns a valuable lesson--what it takes to be a Defender of the Earth.

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: A House Divided
programme.desc: The Phantom's family secret! His evil older brother joins forces with Ming the Merciless and\nbecomes N'Dama - The Weather Demon!

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: Bits And Chips
programme.desc: Ultracomputer Dynak X is invaded by Ming's Electronic Maggot and miniaturized Defenders must fight her war within!

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: The Root Of Evil
programme.desc: A famous scientist's plant food experiment backfire -into a formula that turns people into plants!

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: Cold War
programme.desc: Ming the Merciless develops a weather control device and plots to freeze the world solid!

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: The Sleeper Awakes
programme.desc: A mammoth killer-robot from another galaxy has been buried right under Central City for more than ten million years Ming discovers a way to wake it up!

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: The Revenge Of Astra
programme.desc: The beautiful space princess Astra plans revenge against Flash Gordon--She gives Ming the Merciless her secret formula for a race of unstoppable slaves, The Clay People!

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: The Hall Of Wisdom
programme.desc: The awesome intergalactic storehouse of knowledge visits the Galaxy--and the Defenders must keep Ming from stealing its deadly weapon!

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: The Mind Warrior
programme.desc: Part I - Ming gets control of the Battle Simulation Room, and the Defenders are fighting for real!

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: The Lost Jewels Of Tibet
programme.desc: Mandrake and Lothar join forces with the beautiful Atascadero to find The Lost Jewels of Tibet. They discover, along with Ming, the wrath of a pre-historic dragon.

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: The Mind Warriors (Part II)
programme.desc: Ming utilizes his Star of Mongo crystal to tap Kshin's fertile imagination in the battle simulation room and brings to life "anti" Defenders who can destroy the real Defenders once and for all.

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: The Evil Of Dr. Dark
programme.desc: Ming springs from prison an evil ex-Shadow Lord and nemesis of Mandrake, and orders him to locate the three pieces of the ORB OF KONOS that will enable Dr. Dark to grant the Merciless One immortality.

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: Diamonds Are Ming's Best Friends
programme.desc: Ming plots to steal the Crown Jewels of England so that he can grow invincible crystal soldiers and conquer the world!

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: The Men Of Frost
programme.desc: Ming launches a Frost Satellite with the power to blanket the earth with a veneer of frost and enslave all of humanity.

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: Battleground
programme.desc: Ming uses his freeze-ray weapon to capture unstoppable alien creatures, transport them to earth and unleash them on the world.

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: The Panther Peril
programme.desc: Ming treks to the hidden Temple of Pantheria to acquire the sacred panther tooth which he will use to control the world's panthers, ordering them to wreak havoc on the world and destroy the Defenders!

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: Fury Of The Deep
programme.desc: Ming schemes to take over the earth by using an ocean ographer's invention to turn all the fish in the sea against mankind.

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: Family Reunion
programme.desc: Jedda agrees to become N'Dama's protege, the Weather Demon, in exchange for help in saving her father's life.

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: The Defense Never Rests
programme.desc: Ming develops Android Clones of the Defenders and programs them to commit a series of crimes, so that the real Defenders will be put on trial by the Galactic Federation and banished to a galaxy 300 light years from Earth.

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: Like Father, Like Daughter
programme.desc: In Ming's latest plot, using his Mind Neutralizer to enslave the human race, Ming manipulates his own daughter, Aura, to capture Flash, Rick, Jedda and L.J.

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: The Would Be Defender
programme.desc: When an overzealous 13 year-old superhero wanna-be spends a day at Monitor, it could mean the destruction of earth.

programme.title: Defenders of the Earth: Doorways Into Darkness
programme.desc: Ming captures a powerful source of anti-energy and unleashes an army of monsters from the Nightworld on the earth.

programme.title: Supersize Vs Superskinny
programme.desc: Dr Christian Jessen and Anna Richardson return for a second run of the diet magazine show which tackles the nation’s relationship with food.

programme.title: Supersize Vs Superskinny
programme.desc: Jade weighs just five and half stone, and is desperate to regain her pre-pregnancy size for the sake of her young son. Julie, binges on huge platefuls of home cooked food.

programme.title: Supersize Vs Superskinny

programme.desc: As the competition nears its end, the oven mitts come off and the celebrities fight for a spot in the finale! They face their toughest challenge yet: a cook-off battle called "Tin Foil Chef.".

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Finale the End!
programme.desc: The final two recruits use all the skills they've learned to cook a restaurant-quality meal for a panel of culinary experts. The winning recruit will be awarded $25,000 for their charity.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Can It Really Be This Bad?
programme.desc: 16 of the worst cooks in America — including a sportscaster, a feisty granny and a professional balloon artist — arrive at boot camp with dreams of putting their kitchen nightmares behind them.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Fish Are Food, Not Friends
programme.desc: Mentors Anne Burrell and Tyler Florence introduce the recruits to magical and mysterious kitchen gadgets. Later, boot camp transforms into a fish market where the recruits learn to fillet and prepare fish.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Show Me the Vegetables!

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Game Day!
programme.desc: Recruits compete in cornhole and darts to determine flavors for their craveable game-day creations. For the main dish challenge, mentors Anne Burrell and Tyler Florence teach the recruits how to make irresistible stuffed burgers.

programme.title: Worst Cooks in America: Leftovers Again?
programme.desc: The recruits learn how to create new dishes from common leftover ingredients, then Anne and Tyler leave them alone for the first time to make pizza from scratch. Some pizzas impress the chefs, while others get boxed out.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: These women never get their hands dirty: no blood touched them because they manipulate others to kill for them...but they didn't get away.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Women who kill husbands, lovers, rivals and parents will shock society. But a very special horror is reserved for women who will kill their own.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: A lovely lady with an innocent smile, kind eyes, a charming personality? No one would suspect a woman like that would murder. These women don’t look or behave like killers.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: The heaviest judgments of convicted killers are reserved for those who committed premeditated murder. These women plot and plan. They know the consequences of their actions, but still they go forward to kill.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Under His Control
programme.desc: These are love stories with bleak, bloody endings. Blinded by desire, obsessed and malleable, some women fall into lethal relationships with dangerous, controlling men.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Secrets and Lies
programme.desc: Behind their friendly smiles, deadly women hide histories of bloodshed and murder.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Love Gone Wrong
programme.desc: Love can be beautiful, love can be blind and love can be deadly. Desire and jealousy are powerful forces driving women to dark and horrifying places in their minds.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Married to Murder
programme.desc: To the outside world, their marriages seemed happy. But behind closed doors, there was no domestic bliss. These women wanted out, but getting a divorce wasn’t their preferred option.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Teen Killers
programme.desc: They were too young to drink or vote but they were not too young to commit the most brutal of crimes. Some were driven by pure curiosity: how would it feel to take a life?

programme.title: Deadly Women: Love to Death
programme.desc: Love and money are a beautiful marriage, for the lucky ones they create a life of happiness and ease. Unless the love is of money, the bride is a killer, and the groom their victim.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Kill Their Own
programme.desc: A mother's most basic instinct is to protect her children, to put their needs above her own desire for money, freedom and men. But these deadly women break that sacred bond when they turn against that natural instinct and kill their own offspring.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Obsession
programme.desc: Deciphering what causes minds to corkscrew out of control is the complex work of the criminal profiler. Obsessions can take many forms: beauty, devotion, ego and power.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Hearts of Stone
programme.desc: Deadly Women are not always the ones you expect. They are not the strangers lurking in the dark, they are a young mother, a supportive wife and a grandmother - all killers. Behind their loving masquerade lies a wake of family horror and pain.

programme.title: Deadly Women: Greed
programme.desc: Known as “black widows,” these women kill their spouses, lovers and children for profit. Murder for them becomes a business. Their trade is murder. Their profit? Blood money.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Crimes of revenge are usually single acts of passion. A brew of hatred and restitution boils over in a manic moment of fury. Once caught, revenge killers usually display remorse and atonement.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: No one doubts a woman’s capacity to love, but sometimes lust can turn lethal. In the ultimate fatal attraction, "Deadly Women" looks at cases of murder driven by obsessive love.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: A rifle in a shopping mall, a syringe of potassium chloride and a syringe of insulin, each in the hands of a mentally disturbed woman, lead to the tragic end of many lives.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Judi Buenoano secretly murdered lovers to claim on insurance policies whilst nurse Genene Jones secretly killed at least 46 infants left in her care between 1980 and 1982.

programme.title: Deadly Women
programme.desc: Nurse Beverley Allitt overdosed multiple infants, Stella Nickell poisoned medicine capsules in stores and Kathleen Follbigg killed four of her own children.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Driven to Kill
programme.desc: A serial rapist targeted women. His dark urges raged out of control and led him to murder. He followed a path so random it was impossible to trace, and all that tied him to his crimes were his access to the highways and a bizarre sexual fetish.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Obsession
programme.desc: Power is a responsibility as well as a privilege. But in the wrong hands, power can corrupt. For former Deputy Attorney General for the State of Delaware, losing sight of his sworn oath to uphold justice could prove lethal.

programme.title: The FBI Files: First and Kennedy Street Crew
programme.desc: In the early 1990's, Washington, D.C., became the murder capital of the nation. Few were left untouched by gang violence, which was ignited by the drug trade. By 1994, that violence would strike at the very heart of law enforcement.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Terror In Disguise
programme.desc: Banks use a variety of devices to discourage would-be robbers: security cameras, silent alarms, and exploding dye packs. But when an elusive bank robber targeted Seattle's banks, none of these precautions were effective.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Trail
programme.desc: The disappearance of young women triggered a search that spanned the Pacific Northwest. A massive media campaign failed to locate the drifter, who first charmed then killed them. As investigators followed his trail, he always stayed one step ahead.

programme.title: The FBI Files: The Predator
programme.desc: In the early 1990's, Washington, D.C., became the murder capital of the nation. Few were left untouched by gang violence, which was ignited by the drug trade. By 1994, that violence would strike at the very heart of law enforcement.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Dishonored
programme.desc: Shirley Russell was determined enough to reach the rank of Captain in the United States Marine Corps. When this officer turned up missing, her colleagues refused to believe she had gone AWOL. It was unclear whether Captain Shirley Russell was alive.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Millionaire Murder
programme.desc: A businessman went to Florida to make one last deal before he retired-he never returned home to his millions. Authorities examined who was closest to him and who stood to gain from his disappearance. But this time conventional rules didn't apply.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Business
programme.desc: Many escape the poverty of India to start new lives in the United States. One turned the American dream into a nightmare. People started turning up dead in New York's Indian community-authorities struggled to link fraud and murder to a powerful man.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Temple of Fear
programme.desc: In Miami, the discovery of a mutilated body sent investigators on the trail of a deadly cult. But agents found a wall of silence around the cult's members. Potential witnesses, terrified of reprisals, refused to talk.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Silent Strike
programme.desc: Money may not be the root of all evil, but for some men, a million dollars is enough to justify murder. Even men sworn to uphold the law can sometimes be tempted.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Deadly Stranger
programme.desc: The body of a young woman found burned in a truck launched a manhunt to find her killer. When more bodies began to turn up across the country, the FBI believed the cases were linked. Investigators had a suspect. They just couldn't find him.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Backstage Murder
programme.desc: In the 1980's, two partners created a nightclub that would bring them wealth and international fame. The male strip club phenomenon promised female patrons fun and excitement. But the bright lights hid a dark side.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Under Fire
programme.desc: A series of armored car heists and bloody shoot-outs shocked law enforcement. The brutal violence of the crimes suggested a motive more complex than greed. When the robbers started targeting police, the FBI took charge.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Manhunt
programme.desc: A killer was on the loose in one of America's most popular tourist destinations. Armed and desperate, he evaded law enforcement at every turn. As the Fourth of July weekend quickly approached, thousands of people became potential targets.

programme.title: The FBI Files: Hunter's Target
programme.desc: Over a thousand hunting accidents are reported in the United States each year. Fewer than ten percent of them are fatal. But when one hunter's death seemed suspicious, the FBI was called in to investigate.

programme.title: The FBI Files: No Remorse
programme.desc: A burning body in a dark alley shed light on a cold-blooded killer. His partners in crime would tell the story, if they lived. In the underworld of the drug trade, even a childhood friend can quickly become an enemy.

programme.title: Minds in the Water
programme.desc: The story of one surfer's international journey to help protect dolphins, whales and their ocean environment. Shot on location in Australia, the Galapagos, Chile and Japan, it captures a key moment in one person's life when apathy is no longer an option.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Missing Person
programme.desc: Tragedy unfolds at Westbrook Beach when lifeguards are unable to locate a missing man. The man will be deemed lost at sea if he isn’t found soon, so senior lifeguard Ant takes charge.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: The Festive Season Kicks Off
programme.desc: Durban, South Africa is a hot spot for vacationers during the busy summer season. The season starts on high alert when senior lifeguard Sihle rescues a bather caught in a rip current.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Busiest Day of the Year
programme.desc: New Year’s is the busiest day of the year in Durban. Crowds arrive in hopes that the sea, soft sand and sunshine will cure their hangovers. It's a day of frivolity and endless mishaps.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Powercraft
programme.desc: It's December 31 — a good day for lifeguard trainee Penny to face her fear of big waves. All eyes are on her as she paddles into some of the biggest waves of the season.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Mass Rescue
programme.desc: There's pandemonium at the Wedge when a flash rip sweeps 150 bathers — most of whom can’t swim — off of the sand bank and into deep, treacherous water.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: African Christmas
programme.desc: The fun and festivity of Christmas Day are put on hold after a mass blue bottle jellyfish attack. Lifeguards are forced to close Battery Beach and Country Club.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Day of Reconciliation
programme.desc: The Day of Reconciliation — the first big public holiday of the festive season — starts off damp and overcast. Undeterred, 150,000 vacationers flock to the beaches.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Shark Attack
programme.desc: Five bathers are bitten by an unknown sea creature at the Bay of Plenty, breaking the festive mood and creating a mass panic. Could this be a shark attack?

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Ragers Start the Party
programme.desc: High school graduates, or "ragers," spill onto Umhlanga Beach after partying all night. This beach is plagued by hidden rocks and strong rips — a disaster cocktail for party animals.

programme.title: Durban Beach Rescue: Most Dangerous Beach
programme.desc: Senior lifeguard Luthuli and his “men of steel” work the Wedge, Durban’s most dangerous beach. The shoreline has an unstable sand bank with dangerous holes on either side.

programme.title: Way of the Ocean: Australia
programme.desc: Way of the Ocean Australia explores the connection between man and sea through a visual feast of poetic motion. This wave rich continent provides a breathtaking backdrop to some of the best surfing found on the planet.

programme.title: Surfing Elite (2013)
programme.desc: Surfing Elite The Pro Tape is a surfing movie dedicated to the biggest names in professional surfing. This is the Surfing Elite. These are the shakers and movers of our sport and for good reason.

programme.title: Volcom Stone Presents: BS! (2014)
programme.desc: BS! is an out of the ordinary, if not extraordinary surf film that documents the serious ripping of Dusty Payne, Mitch Coleborn, Alex Gray, Ozzie Wright, Nate Tyler, and Andrew Doheny.

programme.title: Surfing Presents: Du Ciel
programme.desc: This stunning piece of cinema celebrates everything we love about the ocean, including its raw power and ability to put man in his place.

programme.title: Surfer Girlz - Heat Wave
programme.desc: Surfer Girlz Heat Wave interviews the world's best women surfers and even surfing legend Kelly Slater.

programme.title: Surf Skate
programme.desc: What does surfing and skating have in common? If you said, "sick airs" then you would be correct! Surf Skate - Above-the-Lip has plenty of mental surfing and skating airs.

programme.title: Surf Rider Single Fin
programme.desc: Witness some of the most stylish and smile filled rides ever. A classic longboard surf movie for all ages to enjoy. Filmed in high definition with both land and water angles.

programme.title: Surf One

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Cupid in Cuffs
programme.desc: It's the day before Valentine's Day and love is in the air at Da Kine Bail Bonds--but not for Tapi who has failed to appear in court on theft charges. Dog's plan is to have Leland knock on Tapi's door with a Valentine's gift to draw her out.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Bonds of Love
programme.desc: Dog and Beth are finally getting married! They've been together for more than ten years but Dog is determined, as he puts it, to "marry his common law wife the Christian way.".

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: To Love and to Cherish
programme.desc: Dog and Beth are off to the Big Island for their wedding. They hope to relax for a few days but it turns out Leland has a fugitive he needs to catch and despite the time limit, neither Dog nor Beth can resist the opportunity to catch a fugitive.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Bustin' with Justin
programme.desc: Dog and the team must deal with misleading informants, belligerent boaters, and angry drunks when they go after Kimberly, a traffic offender with over 20 violations. And if that isn't enough, Dog has another problem - Duane Lee is sick.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Run Fugitive, Run
programme.desc: When the team hunts for Steven, a fugitive with a history of domestic abuse, they seek help from his girlfriend, who's been a victim of his abuse. Meanwhile, Beth trains for a 5K race to help raise awareness about domestic abuse.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Vegas or Bust
programme.desc: Dog is going to be the keynote speaker at the annual Profession Bail Agents convention in Las Vegas, but before he leaves he's got to clear two cases from his docket - Heidi and Stephanie.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Playing Possum
programme.desc: Tim's got a big problem. Owen has failed to appear in court. He's on bond for serious drug charges and now Tim could lose $30,000 if he doesn't catch Owen. With Dog's help he tries to track down the co-signer but they come up dry.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Rainy Day Woman
programme.desc: It's been raining for days and the team is going a little stir crazy, but Dog has the cure; a good hunt. Maui has failed to appear on a drug charge and the team has just one lead. She was recently spotted during a bust at a local chop shop garage.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Ticket to Ride
programme.desc: Dog decides it's time to outfit the Da Kine crew with new SUVs. After a quick visit to their local dealership, they go after Jasmine, a woman whose criminal record includes over 37 arrests for everything from drug promotion to assault.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Mother Knows Best
programme.desc: Dog has two fugitives to catch, and he gets help from the unlikeliest sources - the fugitives' mothers. First, Ginger's mother wants to revoke her daughter's bond. Then, Brandon's mother decides to revoke his bond because Brandon has an ice habit.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Irons in the Fire
programme.desc: Dog is back hunting in the big city of Denver, but chasing fugitives on the mainland is more dangerous than ever. So Dog decides that the crew should get pepper-ball guns, which have much better range than pepper spray.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Rocky Mountain Roundup
programme.desc: Dog decides to help two of his bondsmen buddies, Dave "Red" Widhelm and "Downtown" Bobby Brown. First up is Red, who has a client, named Alvin, whose bond is $20,000. Then the team goes after Craig, a client of Bobby's whose bond is almost $70,000.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: This One's For You
programme.desc: Dog leads the team on another adrenaline-filled chase in Denver. The fugitive, Robert, has a habit of address-hopping that makes him a difficult target, but Dog refuses to give up and finally tracks Robert down in his latest hideaway.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Baby Lyssa Steps Up
programme.desc: The team is still in Colorado, and today Dog starts his day by to giving his kids and crew a sample of their western heritage by taking them horseback riding. This hunt takes Dog back to his old stomping grounds in Denver.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Running on Empty
programme.desc: Dog's time is running out in Colorado. After a month of helping his bail bondsmen friends around Denver, he's got to get his family back home to Hawaii. But Dog wants one more capture before they leave.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Inside Out
programme.desc: Dog kickstarts the search for Jackson, a 240lbs, six feet tall bad boy who has skipped out on a $10,000 bond. Jackson’s apparently at his father-in-law's house, but the father-in-law has info about Jackson that brings Dog to a unique hideout.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Growing Up Is Hard To Do
programme.desc: With twelve kids of his own, Dog knows how hard it is to keep children on the straight and narrow, especially during their turbulent teens.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Year of the Dog
programme.desc: A one-hour special that looks back at 2006, one of Dog's most tumultuous years, which has included the passing of Beth's father, Dog and Beth's wedding, the tragic death of Dog's daughter Barbara.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Mystery of Mona Lisa
programme.desc: When Lyssa points out that the fugitive in the next case has the same birth date as Barbara, Dog's recently deceased daughter, the team takes a special vow to capture the young woman.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Rusty Cuffs
programme.desc: Dog finds himself fighting two enemies; the law and his inner demons. He continues his legal battle to fight extradition to Mexico in connection with his 2003 capture of fugitive rapist Andrew Luster. His other struggle is private.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Make a Wish
programme.desc: Dog shows his love of justice and children in this poignant episode. He begins by giving encouragement to a group of handicapped children, then starting the search for Jacob, a fugitive who's abandoned his wife and children.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Tough Love
programme.desc: Michael is out on bail for drug sales, theft, and violation of parole. Dog's after him for failing to appear in court and his only lead is Jen, his co-signer and girlfriend.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Surprise Ending
programme.desc: Dog and the boys are going after a fugitive with a $25,000 bond and a string of theft charges behind him. When the team hits his apartment, they find a boot print on the door, a souvenir of a police raid from only days earlier?

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Big Wipe-Out
programme.desc: A Hawaiian surfing hero is on a wave to nowhere and it's Dog's turn to play lifeguard. "Buttons," known throughout the islands for his prowess on the waves and his daring 360's, has wiped-out on the rocky shoals of drug addiction.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: You Can Bet On It!
programme.desc: Kristine had a string of gambling and forgery charges before she jumped bail leaving Dog "holding the bag". Now it's time for Dog to call in some chits of his own, getting the help of trusty informants he's helped out over the years.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Fly Boy
programme.desc: Dog told him not to go, but Charles went anyway, skipping to Oregon against the terms of his bail. Now Dog has a tip that Charles plans to slip back into Honolulu. With $30,000 on the line Dog knows he can leave little to chance.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Guns & Ice
programme.desc: The following day is Dog's birthday but that won't stop him from chasing a fugitive, who is facing firearms charges. Dog doesn't relish the thought of going after an alleged gunslinger on his birthday but he's never one to avoid a challenge.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Good Fight
programme.desc: Dog and Beth have to be at the state capitol bright and early to receive an award for their fight against ice in Hawaii. Afterwards, they're inspired to start the hunt for Shanna, an alleged ice user and identity thief with $80,000 in bonds.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: The Smackdown of Baby Lyssa
programme.desc: After meeting with the cosigner on a bond for a man named John, Dog and the Posse hatch a plan to lure him to a high rise apartment. But when night falls, their plan leaves a member of the team alone and in harm's way!

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: A Friend in Need
programme.desc: Roger has 27 prior arrests, spent years in jail and doesn't want to go back. But he's missed court and now Dog has to bring him in. To complicate matters, this fugitive lives in a tightly-knit community where good information won't come easy.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Your Lying Eyes
programme.desc: Kolani's on the run, left his wife to look after four kids and left Dog holding the bag for the $10k bond. So their pursuit on this case takes them into some parts of Ohau, and the human heart, that few of us will ever see.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Crime Don't Pay
programme.desc: Today the crew is hunting for Holly, a car thief. She's one of Tim's bonds and the entire Dog crew knows that means trouble - or at least a long and difficult chase.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Twisted Love
programme.desc: Dog is tracking down Cecilia, who's wanted for car theft, but she's nowhere to be found. Her girlfriend and co-signer has gone missing too. Just when the trail goes cold, a friend leads the team to the cosigner's empty apartment.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Where the Wild Things Are
programme.desc: Dog, Beth and the team are in Colorado and they face a special challenge - getting the kids to camp. After the drop-off, Dog is more than ready to track down a fugitive. Robin disposed of a body after a homicide, and now he's skipped his court date.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: No Luv Still
programme.desc: Dog is in search of a potentially dangerous fugitive, he's only 19 and charged with kidnapping and menacing. The case takes an unexpected turn when the Chapman clan ends up in a confrontation with the suspect's family.

programme.title: Dog The Bounty Hunter: Day of the Dog
programme.desc: Dog and the team are back in Colorado hunting bounties. Today's fugitive has a long rap sheet and a reputation for packing heat. With nothing but an address and phone number, the team heads out on the hunt.
